File: COVID-19 vaccine. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has paid the deposit to secure the COVID-19 vaccine. This after the country missed the December 15 deadline. READ: 1/5 of the world won't have the COVID vaccine until 2022: study R283-million has been paid to the Vaccine Alliance to secure South Africa’s entry into the COVAX facility. The down payment represents 15-percent of the total cost of securing access to the vaccines. This will enable 10-percent of the population to access the vaccine once it becomes available.